25/09/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Sali Berisha on Wednesday (September 24th) thanked the United States, following the US Senate Foreign Relations Committee's move to sign the protocol for Albania and Croatia's NATO membership. 
"The decision proves our friends' trust in Albania and the Albanian people," Berisha said at a cabinet meeting. 
"I want to assure you that we will make every necessary effort to meet the standards of a NATO member country," he added. 
(Alsat, Telgrafi, Tvsh, Klan, BalkanWeb - 24/09/08)
